Insight Deep Dive — Product Performance

Key Findings

- Beauty leads across all commercial metrics, recording the highest revenue and gross profit among all five product categories, with performance trending consistently upward. This makes Beauty Smart Buy's most valuable and reliable product line.

- Electronics and Groceries present a profitability paradox — despite generating some of the highest revenue figures, both categories return disproportionately low gross profit, signalling significant margin pressure that requires urgent attention.

- Home & Living and Electronics carry the heaviest discount burden, receiving the highest discount allocations across the portfolio. This is directly counterproductive, as deeper discounting is eroding the very profit these categories could otherwise generate.

- Beauty and Fashion operate on the lowest marketing spend, yet both categories deliver strong commercial returns revealing a striking inverse relationship where higher marketing expenditure does not translate into higher revenue, and may in fact be inefficiently allocated across the remaining categories.

- Electronics and Groceries dominate in units sold, recording the highest quantities across the product portfolio. Fashion and Beauty, by contrast, move the fewest units yet generate superior profit, underscoring that volume alone is not a reliable indicator of commercial value.
